cant sell to players cuz who wants a +2 save vs poison ring.  so if think that they should boost the trades so that even if you cant sell back to store for a profit at least make the amount of money you lose only a few silvers or a gold not a couple plat</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Tickedoff</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Not to mention you will NEVER find a high quality bear pelt.  I have been looking for almost 2 months straight, have not leveled at all, just killing bears bears bears and more bears.  I have probably killed over 500 bears but I lost count after 100.  I have found 1 high quality pelt, and bout 2 off other adventurers during this time.  What the hell is wrong with this picture?  NPC Merchants sell unlimited quantities of their wares that would utilize high quality bear pelts, why the hell can't we get more of these pelts to compete?  The players are supposed to be the MASTERS of the trades, not the frickin NPCs.  I've ranted now, and raved, and even raged, but still no high quality bear pelt in sight.  I am about to give up and just dump Everquest now that I've been given my Beta code for Asherons Call.  Maybe just maybe they won't screw things up so bad, but they probably will.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Dawey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">What type of bears are you hunting just out of curiosity? I've found a few high quality bear pelts on kodiaks and Grizzlies. I think I might have even gotten one off of a YK.  Ju</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">mordeas</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">yes make sure you are fighting high enough level bears. if you are fighting cubs or something you will never get them(=. a<BR>try fighting kodiaks. they will give them a lot more often then you say.<P>your friendly mage, mordeas<BR> </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8E